abstract: A move to allow restaurants and other employers to impose tip sharing on workers, and in some cases keep the money, is under fire from labor groups.
snippet: A move to allow restaurants and other employers to impose tip sharing on workers, and in some cases keep the money, is under fire from labor groups.
lead_paragraph: The Trump administration is moving to give restaurants and other employers more control over workers’ tips. But critics have denounced the plan as legalizing wage theft and accuse the administration of suppressing evidence that lends credence to the charge.

abstract: The 400-year history of how we talk about the deserving versus the undeserving poor.
snippet: The 400-year history of how we talk about the deserving versus the undeserving poor.
lead_paragraph: The “able-bodied” are now everywhere among government programs for the poor, Republican officials point out. They’re on food stamps. They’re collecting welfare. They’re living in subsidized housing. And their numbers have swelled on Medicaid, a program that critics say was never designed to serve them.

abstract: The Fed leaves its benchmark interest rate steady, but it signaled that an increase was likely at its next policy meeting in March.
snippet: The Fed leaves its benchmark interest rate steady, but it signaled that an increase was likely at its next policy meeting in March.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve said on Wednesday that it was still trying to stimulate faster economic growth as one of the longest expansions in American history neared the end of its ninth year.
